caption: I only order 1 item, the chicken salad. It's simple, but so tasty and so fresh! Also the owner & staff are all super nice and friendly!
the best chicken i've ever eaten!
Good food and good service. The chicken pita is tasty!!
Love this place.  They know how to cook chicken

Chicken planet has been an icon for almost couple decades in Chi downtown, specifically south loop and famous and loved in the financial corridor, it’s across the St from CBOE/CBOT. Can’t beat the value, yummy fresh chicken, just the right taste and amount with sides at a reasonable price. Their chickeN Pita wrap with their secret sauce is to die for! Love this place, the owner is a great guy super friendly and always helpful throws in a little extra for the regulars all the time. Loved this place, if you are thinking about going there don’t think twice!
Best chicken roll in Chicago!
Amazingly helpful and friendly employees. Great food awesome price.
The lunch chicken roll With cheese is one of the greatest things my taste buds have ever touched. This place is magnificent
Fresh chicken meals with a nice and accommodating staff. I would recommend this restaurant.  If your looking for a quick and tasty lunch option.
Excellent customer service and good chicken
Everyone needs to have a Chicken Planet experience. It's like nothing else this world his to offer. Super tasty chicken that will leave you wanting more.
One of the best grilled chicken dishes in the city! Seasoned to perfection and reasonably priced.  Friendly staff!! Go there
1- chicken- check 2- tasty- check 3- moist- check 4- good price- check 5- fast- check 6- take my money please!
I've been coming to this place for over 20 years. Amazing chicken! Also, try the mild sauce.
Great food and good prices
It was very delicious.
Best chicken i ever tasted
Like chicken? This place is for you. Don't like chicken I would not come here
Best chicken in the city
You like chicken. I like chicken. We all like chicken. This place got some good chicken
Excellent tasty chicken. Portion controls could be relaxed.
Always excellent
Tasty, tender baked chicken. Not much else to say. This is really good chicken and an excellent work lunch to go spot.
Amazing chicken and very fast service!
Tender and juicy chicken
Great food at a good price
Chicken planet is the best. Unique flavor and always fast and friendly.
Great grilled chicken!!
Love the chicken and prices.
Cheap, absolutely delicious, great bargain, total hole-in-the-wall. Love walking in and seeing rows and rows of chickens lined up on the grill
1. Fast 2. Great quantity of food for the price 3. Tastes good
The "chicken roll" aka chicken pita was AMAZING!
It's okay.  The grilled chicken is better than the fried fast food options.
Great food
Favorite grilled chicken place for lunch.  Just wish they would be open on the weekends even if it's just for lunch.
One of the best places for grilled chicken in Chicago...
Best grilled chicken I have tasted - you ought to try it for lunch!
Definitely a lot of chicken. Quick and easy and pretty tasty
Always fresh and delicious
Fantastic lunch spot with pretty good chicken at a really great price.
Great place and prices
Best chicken place in the loop.
Fast and delicious!
Absolutely LOVE the chicken rolls! I have dined here for over 10yrs the food and customer service has always been the same! Tasty 😋. Be mindful lunch hour has a LONG line but worth it.
Chicken roll for an awesome price.  Great work lunch spot.
Best grilled chicken you can get in the downtown area
Great cheap place.
Fantastic value... chicken is juicy! Very happy!
These guys are awesome. Same great taste from last 2 decades almost! It’s always crowded around lunch time but that’s cause they are really good!
Simple menu but they do it right. The chicken is delicious and priced fair. Lunch rush can be very busy so come early to beat the crowd.
Best lunch in the Loop, hands down! Grilled chicken, homemade salsa and BBQ sauce, not much else - it's not needed!
I get an order for the whole modernization crew at Willis Tower every Friday. The chicken rolls are very filling, not to mention delicious!! I highly recommend Chicken Planet frequently!
The chicken is out of this world!!
I liked Chicken Planet.  The chicken was good and served hot.  I liked the coleslaw, it had a vinegar tang to it and the pita was fresh.  I'll be going back.
Good quick food...highly reccomend

One of the best places to get a half chicken off the flame broiled grill. Thats right. Do you miss that barbecue taste? Look no further than Chicken planet. Located downtown Chicago near the L train station
Chicken roll! Happiness on a pita!
Chicken is ready good and moist. Recommend you visit.
Go there and eat great chicken, prices are great, food tasty, the salsa is simply delicious
Awesome tasting chicken.  Good size portion.  Price unbeatable.  Nowhere in Chicago u can get tasty food in large portion for this price
For the price this place is great.  Their grilled chicken salad is generously filled with chicken.  Skip the dressing and get a side of salsa instead.  Delicious and satisfying.

Update: I only get the chicken fingers.  No longer the same quality and consistency that used to make this place great.  Looks to have changed ownership a few times in the last few years.  Used to have a loyalty program that ended.
Best place to have a good,simple, healthy and cheap lunch.
Awesome affordable healthy food
Awesome tasting chicken.  Good size portion.  Price unbeatable.  Nowhere in Chicago u can get tasty food in large portion for this price

Half a chicken, a side, and pita for less than $7. Can't beat it downtown in the Loop. Flavorful chicken is what they do best and they do it fast and friendly in a small place; don't plan on eating there, you're better off getting it to go and eating elsewhere with limited seating.
A healthy, delicious meal. The chicken was flavorful and juicy, the pita was great, I just finished my meal and I can't wait to come back
A generous portion of food for around $5, and you can receive it within seconds of ordering
If you like grilled chicken pita’s come here. The BBQ is quality and the food is very fresh. Just watch out for the line at 12:15-12:45. There is limited seating as well.  Overall food - 9/10.
Go to place for a quick, cheap but quality lunch if you're in the loop.
Not the best chicken I've ever eaten but for the price it is pretty good I don't have any complaints
Awesomely delicious & healthy grilled Mediterranean/Greek styled chicken; addictingly good
Great food, great price!
Great chicken salad every time  🥗

Great food! Grilled/roasted chicken, not fried! Popular menu items are the $6 Lunch Roll & $6 Quarter chicken Dark with a side of mashed potatoes or cole slaw or rice and pita bread! Sauce options are a mild bbq sauce or salsa verde.  UBER DELICIOUS!  😋
Great experience every visit
Best lunch for the money in the loop

Chicken is tender and moist (even the white meat).  Chicken sandwich is very good and it is easy to eat 2 of them (3 for very hungry people).  Price is very cheap so very good value.  Place is busy, and no AC so in summer it will be hot.  There are a couple tables to eat at.

Me and my crew have been looking for this restaurant since 2010. They moved from Jackson and State and we missed them dearly. Wow!!! The food was great!!! Grilled chicken, yellow rice, mashed potatoes, pita bread. I feel like we hit the lottery and even though we have moved miles away, we will be there to place our orders.  WE ALL ARE SOOOOO GLAD WE FOUND YOU CHICKEN PLANET!!!!!!:-)
Chicken planet is the go to spot for lunch in the loop!
Best grilled Chicago has to offer since moving here
Decent, great prices
Yeah buddy! Go git some of that!

Chicken Planet is a good place to eat.  They have about 20 full chickens cooking on the grill at a time.  I most of the time get the 1/2 chicken plate.  The sauces they have are good to.  I have no problem going back for more.
Great sandwiches
Been here a handful of times. Love the chicken lunch specials.
Good chicken salad you can have in downtown
Great place for a protein filled lunch. The pita bread is amazing.
(Translated by Google) The chicken is simply delicious.  (Original) El chicken es simplemente  delicioso.

An excellent place for grilled chicken. As the name suggests, they only do chicken here, but you can get it grilled, in a salad, or a chicken soup. The quality of food is very good, their sides are delicious, and the price is great. A quarter white meal will only set you back $6... Being in the loop, this is extremely cheap, compared to similar places there. I would definitely recommend it.
Great tasting priced without the greed. Way to go!
Cheap prices, fast service, really good chicken
Really delicious lunch.
Cheap, delicious, and very efficient. I usually got the chicken roll but would share a half chicken with coworkers sometimes. Good value.

The service here is fast. Its very congested and crowded though. The quantity for the money paid is very high. I personally did not like the taste but I guess it tickles the taste buds for many. I wouldn't complain.
Best chicken on the planet
Great lunch spot. Delicious food at a great price in the loop.
Great chicken and great prices!
Cheapest food in the area. Quickest food in the area. Above average food for the area.
This is a great place to get a simple quick lunch. Half a chicken, rice or mashed potatoes and a drink for $6!
Greatest roasted chicken!!

Chicken was over cooked and less than decent. Service was great and I got my food right away so thats a plus. Mashed potatoes and pita was good. However,  I expect a place with grilled chicken to be tender and juicy and it was drier than the Sahara at times; luckily I had the BBQ sauce to compliment it. If you're looking for chicken that will smack you across the face with how good and tasty it is look elsewhere. The seasoning was too bland and any person of color with actual taste buds shouldn't come here. I'm hoping I just got an order that was already prepared because all you people giving it 5 stars really don't know what good chicken is.
Good food with fair servings at great prices. Its hard to find a lunch as cheap and good as this in this area.
One of the best lunch places in the loop. I live for being called 'Chief' or 'Boss'
Chicken is just good.
Great chicken, great prices!
Incredible price, speed and taste.
Chicken was delicious, hot, and reasonably priced.  Line looks worse than it is.
Great downtown spot for lunch!
Great place for fresh chicken
Good chicken at reasonable price. But a bit more expensive in its newer location than previously
(Translated by Google) Great chicken bawk bawk !!  (Original) Great chicken bawk bawk!!
Best easy, healthy option in this crowded area. The owner behind the counter is a nice man. Cheap and quick, but pretty good. What's better than that?
Good grilled chicken, served fast and good value. Where else can you get 1/2 chicken with rice a pita, salsa and BBQ sauce, and a fountain drink for $8.  Oh, did I mention this is in the loop.
simple quick and fast good and  cheap
Cheap large meal
Great roasted chicken
Best deal in all of downtown Chicago.
Best chicken in the loop! It's a dive with only very limited seating, but the food is incredible and very cheap. It's a small menu, but everything is great.
Best chicken deal in the area.
Solid chicken at a reasonable price
The chicken is so delicious and the rice is amazing.
Efficient, Quality food. Prepared quickly and at a great price

The chicken is fantastic.  If you like grilled chicken that is done really well this is the place to go.  Super good chicken.  Great prices too.  That said all the sides they serve are terrible (that cannot be overstated) and the BBQ sauce they give you is about the worst BBQ sauce on the planet.  Go for the chicken...forget the rest. (I'd totally be willing pay more for better sides.)

When I first brought home food from Chicken Planet, I was laughed at because of the name. Then they tried the food. Chicken Planet is simple and relatively cheap in comparison to other places to eat in Chicago. You can also stay moderately healthy eating here. While they don't have a significant amount of variety, Chicken Planet is the best at what it does. Chicken.
Favorite lunch spot in the city. Very limited dine in options but for the price, you can't beat this place. Excellent chick options.
If you're a vegetarian, get the corn on the cob here. It's the best!
If you like chicken, this is the place to go. Great value.
I love love love their grilled chicken. Super tasty and cheap.

The menu is straight forward and simple. Chicken. Quarter, half or in a wrap. Potato salad or rice. I love it! Wonderful portions! Even better prices! The line is always out the door during the lunch rush BUT it always moves quickly.
nice
Good, cheap, juicy grilled chicken
Friendly staff, chicken always seems bland to me. But its a quick and cheap.
Only the best
Great food, cheap prices.  Friendly staff.
Best chicken in the Chicagoland area!
Just like the other reviews say, this chicken is really good. Super affordable for the loop too!
Best chicken ever!
Solid meal for around $8, which isn't too common in the loop these days.
Place rocks.  You get a lot for your money at this place and the chicken is cooked perfectly.  Should have bought the place years back when the owner offered to sell it.
This place is probably my favorite lunch place downtown. It's delicious and it's quick.
Sells chicken and only chicken, so they do it pretty damn well. The half and quarter chickens are great but the chicken roll can be slightly dry.
Must go spot if u like lots of grill chicken!

Chicken and chicken only. Cheapest meal you can get in the loop that isn't "fast food". I assimilate this restaurant when I was ill and cannot stomach it anymore. Personal thing, but I would eat it more if it wasn't for that.
The most efficient chicken butchers in the world. These guys know chicken. and they know how to get it in your hands in minutes, grilled fresh, with amazing sides, and all during the lunch rush.
Chicken rolls are great!  Price is excellent!
This place was a nice spot to grab n go. The service was quick and the food was decent. You get what you pay for.

This place really won me over. The first time that discovered it, there was hardly anyone inside, I took that on face value and choose to eat at a busier (read: more popular) establishment. Passed by on another (cold!) day during lunch hour, and was surprised by the long line almost out of the door. Short on time, it took a 3rd day before I finally went in and ordered the chicken salad. Its been the same 2-3 times a week for 3 months now, and the chicken salad is always fast, fresh and filling! I havent tried anything else on the menu yet, so i won't speak to those items, as the public has already so convincingly spoken.  Great for a quick break, yet expect the place to be quite busy during peaks: the line can extend out of the door (not a bad thing at all, more like a good sign). Even during rush hours the staff is patient and efficient. Haven't had a bad experience in the last 3 months and have recommended them more than a few times. Here's the online version,
Excellent

I try to go to this place every week. This place is a nice hole in the wall place with some awesome chicken. It's basically a carry out place although they do have very limited seating capacity. Their chicken is awesome and tastes real good. I'll recommend every one working in the south loop to try this place out.
Great lunch spot.  Lines may look long, but they move fast.

I get lunch here at least once a week, and it is one of the best places around for tasty and healthy grilled chicken. The dark is very tender and moist.  You might see the line running very long, but don't be intimidated. The service is quite fast, as they have an industrial-sized grill right behind the counter, churning the chicken out very efficiently.  5 stars for taste and service!

I started the chicken goes it's pretty good the thing that keeps you coming is a great deal for about 6 bucks you can get half a chicken two sides bread and a drink you really can't beat that price in the loop so he looking for a good deal with good food try out this place

This place is a once a week must eat for me.  The price you pay for what you get is just amazing. My two favorites are the half chicken meal that comes with a side and pita bread or the chicken wrap. Both of these items cost less that 6.00, great prices and unbelievable food.﻿

Delicious, fast, and inexpensive. What more could you want from lunch in the Loop. It's only 8 bucks for a half of a chicken, side, and a drink. Don't be fooled by a long line, they churn customers like things that are churned quickly.
Excellent! Had the chicken roll.
Walked about 20 minutes to get the chicken. It was totally worth it, got our food in less than a minute
Now this is a hidden gem!  I wish I could have this everyday however being mainly a fried chicken place, it's not the healthiest places to eat but, definitely go once in a while!

This place doesn't look like much but their chicken is amazing and it's pretty affordable for the area. I didn't think the sides that came with it were all that great. I wouldn't get any next time and just eat the delicious chicken!
I've never had a bad experience eating here. The food is decently priced, the wait time is short (even with a line), and the workers are friendly. Definitely try this place out!
Chicken is phenomenal- esp for the price!

Great value for your lunch! The food is fresh, tasty and super affordable!  All of their sides I tasted have been great, please keep in mind the side portions are huge! Another one of my favs is the chicken roll- only $5.25; that is with tax!
Quick and Cheap, the Chicken salad is huge with lots of Chicken in a big salad.

Affordable, affordable chicken! As soon as you walk into this place you'll be greeted by the smell of freshly grilled chicken on the grill. Quarter chicken, half chicken, dark, white, mixed and your option of sides including rice, potatoes, slaw or corn. Split a whole chicken with a friend with two sides for about $11 and you're all set! I really recommend this place as a quick stop in for a good lunch, and seating may get hard to find so look to bring it back if you're on lunch or sit outdoors. Make sure to get tons of napkins because you'll be finger lickin' after gnawing on these birds!
Great Food with Amazing prices.
One of the best lunches for the money in the South Loop. Great chicken, grilled perfectly, reasonable sides, plenty of options, quick service, nice staff.  What's not to love?

The chicken is great and the prices are very reasonable.  The only downside is their sides are terrible as is their BBQ sauce.  Really, really underwhelming.  Mashed potatoes are runny and bland.  The rice nearly flavorless.  The corn boiled/steamed to hell and back (and too small a portion).  And runny, boring BBQ sauce.  If they sorted out their sides and provided good quality and tasty ones this place would probably have lines around the block every day.
This food is great but place is rather small.
Great value for a lot of food.  Chicken is always tasty and sides are decent.
I love chicken and love this place. The chicken roll is good and I love that it really has a lot of chicken, not mostly salad and sauce like in some other places.
No room to sit, but hands-down the best chicken in the Chicagoland area.

Great local place for lunch downtown. I used to work in the Sears Tower and come over here. My company moved farther away but I still occasionally make the trek down to get some chicken. You can either get a chicken meal where they cut the chicken up, or get a chicken roll. I've found the chicken roll can be dry so I definitely recommend the quarter or half chicken meals.

This is seriously the best value in the city.  I try to make it here every week during lunch and order a chicken roll.  It's a hole in the wall place that is affordable with almost any budget and has some of the quality of a fancy restaurant. Even if the line looks long, don't be discouraged because you'll be in and out in under 10 minutes.

Food was great and were very fast. Prices were cheap and the staff was very friendly and helpful as to what to order. Recomomend going there when by the sears tower. Much cheaper that other restaurants around it.
Chicken Planet is great! They give good portions for little cost! Much of their food like a healthy version of KFC! There may be a line when you go but I would deffinetly recomend it!
Great food!  Fresh grilled chicken at a reasonable price and the sides are made fresh everyday.  My favorite is their quarter chicken meal with a side of mashed and a drink.  Less than $5!
Highly recommend.
Chicken has no flavor so get a sauce on the side.
Good quantity and worth the money.  Very helpful if u need a quick bite to eat.
For the grilled chicken fix without the heavy bbq sauce or deep fried flavor.  A great value.  The eating area is just small, so setting can be iffy.
Simply the finest chicken in Chicago.  Absurdly good.
Best chicken ever.  It's one of those restaurants that breaks down every race, class, age, and gender barrier, all in the name of delicious chicken.
